
** Bio3D package source code
The most recent version of the Bio3D package is in the dir "ver_devl/"
All previous versions are in a seperate dir with their version number.

See the '00EDITS' file in ver_devl/ dir for recent changes (i.e. changes 
from last version), otherwise refer to wiki page:
   http://bio3d.pbworks.com/w/page/7824486/WhatsNew

** Update steps
See the wki page:
   http://bio3d.pbworks.com/w/page/7824480/ToDo

These notes are also pasted below.

Make your desired changes to the development version of the package 
  (see: Rpackage/ver_devel/ ).

Then follow these steps:
- Update the version number in the file "bio3d/DESCRIPTION".
- Update the version number in the file "bio3d/man/bio3d.package.Rd"
- Remove the old tar.gz version of the package "rm bio3d_1.0-?.tar.gz"
- Build a new version with "R CMD build bio3d"
- Run "R CMD check bio3d"
- Remove your old bio3d installation "R CMD REMOVE bio3d"
- Install the new version "sudo R CMD INSTALL bio3d_1.0-?.tar.gz"

- Assuming everything works, then add to older mccammon website: 
  "scp bio3d_1.1-?.tar.gz bgrant@chemcca3.ucsd.edu:~/public_html/bio3d/."

- Add to new grantlab.org website:  
  "scp bio3d_1.1-4.tar.gz thegr020@shell.guardedhost.com:/webroot/t/h/thegr020/thegrantlab.org/www/bio3d/. "

  and to Dropbox alternate download site: "cp bio3d_1.1-4.tar.gz ~/Dropbox/Public/. " 

- Make a windows .zip version by changing to your package library dir 
  (see .libPaths() output):  
  "cd /Library/Frameworks/R.framework/Versions/2.14/Resources/library"

  Run zip -r bio3d_1.0-?.zip bio3d
  Copy the zip file to the web space or windows box for testing 
  "scp bio3d_1.1-4.zip bgrant@chemcca3.ucsd.edu:~/public_html/bio3d/."
  "scp bio3d_1.1-4.zip thegr020@shell.guardedhost.com:/webroot/t/h/thegr020/thegrantlab.org/www/bio3d/."

- Update the webpage links accordingly 
  (see ~/public_html/bio3d/download/download.html and 
  /webroot/t/h/thegr020/thegrantlab.org/www/bio3d/download/download.html ).

- Update the package manual and other documentation.

  To make the manual run "R CMD Rd2pdf --pdf --title="The bio3d Package" bio3d"
  Copy this pdf to the web site
  "scp bio3d.pdf thegr020@shell.guardedhost.com:/webroot/t/h/thegr020/thegrantlab.org/www/bio3d/." and
  "scp bio3d.pdf  bgrant@chemcca3.ucsd.edu:~/public_html/bio3d/." 

- Copy html doc pages to web site *** UPDATE/EDIT THIS ***
  "cp /net/home/bgrant/software/R-local/R-2.7.2/library/bio3d/html/* ~/public_html/bio3d/html/."

- Add links to new html doc pages on the main docs.tml web site page "emacs ~/public_html/bio3d/docs/docs.html &"

- Comment on changes in the wiki here
  "http://bio3d.pbworks.com/w/page/7824486/WhatsNew"

